istered User</span><br>  Posts: 538<br> <font color=#000000>(11/15/02 2:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ftmalliance99801frm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=41.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Shadowblade question...</span><hr size=1> Question on speccing.  I am thinking about making a shadowzerker (low crit strike, high axe, high left axe).  What levels do you have crit strike and envenom at?  I know stealth should be at least 16 by 24, for detect hidden, but what about the other skills?<br>
<br>
Any help is appreciated. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#EBEFF1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/btmalliance99801.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lux028>Lux028</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#000000>(11/20/02 12:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ftmalliance99801frm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=41.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Shadowblade question...</span><hr size=1> Well 21 in crit strike gives you perforate artery, 18 in CS gives you garrote (assassin bread n' butter any-time style). Unless you want either of those, you probably just want to dump points in axe and left axe with remainder in envenom.  Might as well get back stab 2 though just in case you see a nice juicy caster sitting there and your 2hander is burning a hole in your pocket...erm...I mean... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFF0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/btmalliance99801.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ashreq>AshrEQ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 549<br> <font color=#000000>(11/21/02 11:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ftmalliance99801frm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=41.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Shadowblade question...</span><hr size=1> With the new auto-equip changes, is switching from 2h to 2-1h easier?  I.e. does it auto-equip your left-handed weapon like it does with shields? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#EBEFF1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/btmalliance99801.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lotsolance>Lotsolance</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  